      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "marklower links live in **JSON instance space**, in three flavours. Jump to the\ndocument-relative links subchapter at [/[2]](/[2]), the project-root one\nat [/[3]](/[3]), or external links at [/[4]](/[4]) — each\nits own subchapter below.\n",
          "array": false,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": []
        }
      },
      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "Wherever you are in this guide, the top of it at [/[0]](/[0]) is one\ndocument-relative link away. You can also leave for the wider world, like the KaTeX\nproject at [https://katex.org](https://katex.org).\n",
          "array": false,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": []
        }
      },
      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "Document-relative links",
          "array": true,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": [
            {
              "key": null,
              "edge": "contain",
              "value": {
                "kind": "scalar",
                "value": "A `/path` link is relative to **this document** — the whole guide — however deep you\nare reading. So [/[0]](/[0]) always lands on the opening line.\n",
                "array": false,
                "set": false,
                "anchors": [],
                "entries": []
              }
            },
            {
              "key": null,
              "edge": "contain",
              "value": {
                "kind": "scalar",
                "value": "From here, reach a sibling section at [/[3]](/[3]), or descend deeper\nto [/[2][2]](/[2][2]).\n",
                "array": false,
                "set": false,
                "anchors": [],
                "entries": []
              }
            },
            {
              "key": null,
              "edge": "contain",
              "value": {
                "kind": "scalar",
                "value": "Going deeper",
                "array": true,
                "set": false,
                "anchors": [],
                "entries": [
                  {
                    "key": null,
                    "edge": "contain",
                    "value": {
                      "kind": "scalar",
                      "value": "Even two levels down, a `/…` link still counts from the document root: the intro at\n[/[0]](/[0]), and the external-links section at [/[4]](/[4]).\n",
                      "array": false,
                      "set": false,
                      "anchors": [],
                      "entries": []
                    }
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "Project-root links",
          "array": true,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": [
            {
              "key": null,
              "edge": "contain",
              "value": {
                "kind": "scalar",
                "value": "A `//path` link is relative to the **project root** — the directory you served. Served\nfrom the repo, a sibling example is at [//examples/68-math-chapter](//examples/68-math-chapter),\nor one formula in it at [//examples/68-math-chapter/[2]](//examples/68-math-chapter/[2]).\n",
                "array": false,
                "set": false,
                "anchors": [],
                "entries": []
              }
            },
            {
              "key": null,
              "edge": "contain",
              "value": {
                "kind": "scalar",
                "value": "The pet handbook is at [//examples/66-pet-keeper-handbook](//examples/66-pet-keeper-handbook). To return home,\nregardless of mount point, use a document-relative link to this guide's intro at\n[/[0]](/[0]).\n",
                "array": false,
                "set": false,
                "anchors": [],
                "entries": []
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "key": null,
        "edge": "contain",
        "value": {
          "kind": "scalar",
          "value": "External links",
          "array": true,
          "set": false,
          "anchors": [],
          "entries": [
            {
              "key": null,
              "edge": "contain",
              "value": {
                "kind": "scalar",
                "value": "Any target with a scheme is an external link, opened in a new tab: Wikipedia on\nhyperlinks at [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperlink](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperlink),\nor email the maintainer at [mailto:dimskraft@gmail.com](mailto:dimskraft@gmail.com).\n",
                "array": false,
